To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Tennessee Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

•	Any document(s) related to automatic license plate reader (ALPR) system use and coordination with the Carter County Sheriff’s Department;
•	Any document(s) related to state ALPR system(s) located within Carter County;
•	Any policy document(s) on state access to ALPR system(s) data of municipalities or counties.
•	Any procurement document(s) related to the installation and use of any ALPR system in Carter County;
•	All contract(s), memorandum of understanding(s) or other agreement(s) for any ALPR provider system in Carter County;
•	Document(s)/information relating to any ALPR system camera numbers in active use, planned and installation locations and dates in Carter County;
•	Permit(s) for use of any ALPR system(s) in Carter County;
•	Name(s)/number(s) of any ALPR camera model(s) in active use in Carter County ;
•	Name(s) of “hot list(s)” or “watch list(s)” created and in use in any ALPR system in Carter County;
•	Name(s) of all agencies with which any Carter County ALPR data is shared; 
•	Carter County ALPR system data access agreement(s) with any private business(es), homeowner association(s), third part(ies) or individual(s);
•	Any ALPR system data retention policy;
•	Number of license plates scanned for the last 30 days with any ALPR system(s) in Carter County;
•	Number of “hits” on “hot” or “watch list(s)” for the last 30 days in any ALPR system in Carter County;
•	Number of times any Carter County ALPR system(s) were accessed/searched and for what reason during the last 30 days;
•	Any Carter County ALPR system audit log(s)/record(s) for the last 30 days;
•	Memorandum(s), note(s), electronic-mail regarding public notification of implementation of any ALPR system in Carter County;
•	Any formal public release notice(s) regarding implementation of any ALPR system in Carter County.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kent Hoover, a citizen of Tennessee, in coordination with Elizabethton Surveillance.

