•	Authorization(s)/agreement(s) with the Tennessee Department of Transportation for Flock Safety/ALPR system;
•	Name(s)/number(s) of Flock Safety/ALPR camera model(s) in active use;
•	Name(s) of “hot list(s)” or “watch list(s)” created and in use in the Flock Safety/ALPR system;
•	Name(s) of all agencies with which ALPR data is shared with other users of the Flock Safety/ALPR system; 
•	Name(s) of all agencies from which data is received through the Flock Safety/ALPR system;
•	All Flock Safety/ALPR system data access agreement(s) with any private business(es), homeowner association(s), third part(ies) or individual(s);
•	Any documentation with Lowes regarding access to that company’s Flock Safety/ALPR system data;
•	Flock Safety/ALPR system data retention policy;
•	Number of license plates scanned with the Flock Safety/ALPR system for the last 30 days;
•	Number of “hits” on “hot” or “watch list(s)” in the Flock Safety/ALPR system for the last 30 days;
•	Number of times Flock Safety/ALPR system data was accessed/searched and for what reason for the last 30 days;
•	Flock Safety/ALPR system audit log(s)/record(s) for the last 30 days;
•	Policy regarding access misuse of Flock Safety/ALPR system;
•	Officer disciplinary record(s) for abusing access to and use of Flock Safety/ALPR system data;
•	Policy on printing (or otherwise capturing or imaging) data from the Flock Safety/ALPR system;
•	Policy regarding transparency of Flock Safety/ALPR statistics (non-personal identification) with the public/citizens;
•	Memorandum(s), note(s), electronic-mail regarding public notification of implementation of Flock Safety/ALPR system;
•	Any formal public release notice(s) regarding implementation of Flock Safety/ALPR system.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kent Hoover, a citizen of Tennessee, in coordination with Elizabethton Surveillance.

